'''The Mall Blackburn''', also known by its former name '''Blackburn Shopping Centre''', is a [[shopping centre]] that serves the town of [[Blackburn]], [[Lancashire]] [[England]] and is owned by [[The Mall Company]].
==History== The shopping centre was built in three phases of which the final one opened in 1979. In 1995 the centre was refurbished during which the lower floor of the former Co-operative department store was transformed into Ainsworth Mall.
===Modernization=== As with many other 'The Mall' shopping centres, The Mall Blackburn has undergone a massive or 'monster' development modernization project. TV screens, 'Ask Me' points and other enhanced information is already provided and brand new areas such as a [[WHSmith]] and [[Primark]] has been built and opened on 26 July 2010.
As well as the modernization of the shopping centre, [[The Mall Company]] has introduced 'spend me' cards which are available.<ref>[http://www.thebee.co.uk/news.php 107 The Bee information on 'Spend Me' cards]</ref>
==Transport links== The shopping centre is located in the centre of [[Blackburn]] and is a short walk to: *[[Blackburn railway station]] *[[Blackburn Boulevard bus station]] * Blackburn Taxi Ranks
